meta_description: Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teet
short_description: Features & Benefits  Very little friction created while cutting due to the unique metallurgy of the blades, transfering heat away from the work-piece so it can be immediately handled Hardly any vibration. Feels like cutting through wood rather than steel Blades range from 5-3/8" to 14" (137-356mm) in diameter Blades reach their full potential when used on special metal cutting circular saws Designed to cut angle iron, c-channel, steel plate, thin steel, trusses, rebar, joists, conduit, grading, and aluminum Tungsten carbide tipped blade for longer blade life
summary: Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teeth on the blade, carbide grade and the shape of the teeth. (1) per card

meta_description: Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teet
description: 12" 60TPI Blade for Steel, 1" Arbor
short_description: Features & Benefits  Very little friction created while cutting due to the unique metallurgy of the blades, transfering heat away from the work-piece so it can be immediately handled Hardly any vibration. Feels like cutting through wood rather than steel Blades range from 5-3/8" to 14" (137-356mm) in diameter Blades reach their full potential when used on special metal cutting circular saws Designed to cut angle iron, c-channel, steel plate, thin steel, trusses, rebar, joists, conduit, grading, and aluminum Tungsten carbide tipped blade for longer blade life
summary: Metal Devil® metal cutting circular saw blades are designed with different configurations for steel, stainless, aluminum, thin steel, and even steel studs. Important differences between blade configuration allow for specialty applications - number of teeth on the blade, carbide grade and the shape of the teeth. (1) per card

category_names: Hole Saw - Metal Drill Bits|Hole Saws
meta_description: This premium line of professional quality hole saws features an M3 high-speed steel cutting edge, electron beam welded to a tough steel backer. Caps stand up to abuse and punishment, yet are lighter and easier to use than those of competitors. Positive ra
short_description: This premium line of professional quality hole saws features an M3 high-speed steel cutting edge, electron beam welded to a tough steel backer. Caps stand up to abuse and punishment, yet are lighter and easier to use than those of competitors. Positive rake tooth design provides better chip clearance as teeth cut into wood, plastic or any machinable metal.   Backer, cutting edge and cap work together to provide faster, longer-lasting cutting action Bi-metal design bonds M3 cutting edge to fatigue resistant backer Positive rake teeth clear chips better for longer life and easier cutting Teeth stay sharper and make smoother cuts
